context: On the 1st of January 1901 the <a0_0><b4_0>nation-state of Australia officially came into existence as a federation<b4_0/><a0_0/>. The Australian continent was colonised by the United Kingdom in <a1_0><b5_0><b6_0>1788<b6_0/><b5_0/><a1_0/>, which subsequently established <a3_0><b8_0>six, eventually self-governing, colonies<b8_0/><a3_0/> there. In the 1890s the governments of these colonies all held referendums on becoming a unified, self-governing "Commonwealth" within the British Empire. When all the colonies voted in favour of federation, the Federation of Australia commenced, resulting in the establishment of the Commonwealth of Australia in 1901. The model of Australian federalism adheres closely to the original model of the <a2_0><b7_0>United States of America<b7_0/><a2_0/>, although it does so through a parliamentary Westminster system rather than a presidential system.
